00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:28.000
[Amit Varma]: Welcome to the Scene and the Unseen.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.520
[Amit Varma]: who's been writing about economics and covering the government for over 17 years now. Pooja

00:01:32.520 --> 00:01:37.040
[Amit Varma]: has been the economics editor of the Hindu and has won the Ramnath Goenka Excellence

00:01:37.040 --> 00:01:43.440
[Amit Varma]: in Journalism Award in 2008 and 2009. And she's just released a fascinating book called

00:01:43.440 --> 00:01:50.800
[Amit Varma]: India's Lost Decade, which chronicles the 10 years between 2008 and 2018, and describes

00:01:50.800 --> 00:01:56.100
[Amit Varma]: how those were years of lost potential for us, in which a series of bad decisions by

00:01:56.100 --> 00:02:01.880
[Amit Varma]: multiple Prime Ministers and multiple Finance Ministers harmed the Indian economy, and by

00:02:01.880 --> 00:02:06.920
[Amit Varma]: extension, millions of Indians, especially the poor. I've admired Pooja's writing on

00:02:06.920 --> 00:02:12.360
[Amit Varma]: economics for a long time, and I picked up the book expecting a really good read on economics.

00:02:12.360 --> 00:02:17.320
[Amit Varma]: But it's a lot more than that. Firstly, the thrust of the book is the impact of politics

00:02:17.320 --> 00:02:22.480
[Amit Varma]: on economics and is filled with political insight. Secondly, the book is packed with

00:02:22.480 --> 00:02:27.440
[Amit Varma]: human drama. Of the sort, the likes of Shakespeare would have turned into multiple plays. Like

00:02:27.440 --> 00:02:32.960
[Amit Varma]: my God, this book is tales of so many petty resentments, grand ambitions, mad delusions,

00:02:32.960 --> 00:02:38.680
[Amit Varma]: petty lint arrogance, and a series of human follies that are all the rational acts of

00:02:38.680 --> 00:02:42.840
[Amit Varma]: flawed humans. It's fascinating and I was delighted when Pooja agreed to come and chat

00:02:42.840 --> 00:02:47.720
[Amit Varma]: with me about the book. Just one thing though, our conversation was recorded over Skype over

00:02:47.720 --> 00:02:53.000
